		<!-- Start: CommunityServer.Discussions.Controls.PostDisplay.TextPost -->
<!-- Skin Path: /Themes/default/Skins/PostType-TextPost.ascx -->
No light at the end of the tunnel, Trolls are as good in the early game as they are at the end.  You see no huge gains later like the small races do with 2hb AA or the bigger HP additions.  

Trolls are a solid Race, we have a 61 Troll SK in my Guild who just Tanked Executioner Trial.  The fact that he survived and won surprised many.  At that point he's a very solid tank, and even though I think he looses DPS to more intelligent Races do to their higher mana pool, he's no slouch.

The regen at higher levels is really a non issue.  Unless you constantly go in Skell form (which negates all your Large Race bonuses) the HP replacement just isn't enough to make a big difference once you have 4k HP's

The one piece of advice I'd add is to make sure you keep at least 1 1 hand weapon skill maxed.  A sword and shield is a HUGE help along the way for extra tanking power and resist gear as needed.

Neptunis Rex
lvl 62 DE Gravelord

